snippet.textDisplay:
When I first heard it... I was like... "meeh.. Not quite". I think that's because some other amazing songs came from coke studio and this one wasn't quite up to expectation. But as I listen to it more, I think it's quite good. I even came to like Asim Azhar's part, which is quite a shock to myself, cause I didn't initially like the song because of him. 
It's undeniable, the song just gets to you. 

But one thing though, as a logical person it's hard to miss, the girls vocal and lyrics both are so much deeper and sophisticated than the guys. 

Especially the lyrics, it's hard to miss,  at the end it feels like the girl is saying something from the deepest of her heart and the guys just teasing and (if you will...) flirting. 

Not quite a successful duet, lyrically speaking. 
I just gave it a like though :-\ 
I guess the critique part of me doesn't like the song, but I guess I like it.
